member_experience_collection.title: Data Scientist
member_experience_collection.location: Région de New York City, États-Unis
member_experience_collection.company_name: Societe Generale Corporate and Investment Banking - SGCIB
member_experience_collection.description:
Develop data driven tools to improve risk monitoring effectiveness, increase process efficiency, reduce operational cost and operational risks, using machine learning technics.

●● Credit Risk ●●
- Design of a machine learning algorithm to adjust the goodness of fit of early warning indicators to optimize the monitoring of counterparties with deteriorating credits.
- Early Warning Indicator Ecosystem redesign and processes automation

▶ Statistics/Algebra/ML:
- Machine Learning: OLS, Logistic Regression, KMeans, KNN, SVM/C, RNN, LSTM, CNN, GradientBoosting, LGBM, AdaBoost, Random Forest, TensorFlow, Keras, ScikitLearn, pipelines.
Data Acquisition, SMOTE, Model Selection, Features Selection, Prediction, BackTesting, Deployment.
- Model back testing: WTI Oil and HH Gas commodities Price and Provision Deck back testing – Data acquisition, analytics.
- Hypothesis tests

●● Operational Risk ●●
- Analytics on key indicators

▶ Data:
- Data Analytics - Python (pandas, jupyter, numpy, scipy), Matlab, ElasticSearch technology
- Chatbot development - Python
- BI: Microsoft Power BI, Microstrategy, Tableau
- Dataviz : d3js, matplotlib, seaborn
- Big Data (Hadoop, PySpark)
- NLP: spacy, nltk
- NoSQL, MongoDB, ElasticSearch

●●Entreprise Risk ●●
- Development of a tool to automate the escalation of RAS metrics,
- Design of the Stress Test Database – SQL, Python, VBA

▶ Dev/SI Architecture:
- REST API and SOA
- Cloud architectures, virtualization, Docker, Kubernetes
- Development: Back: JEE, Python Flask, Django - Front: Angular
- Automation: Python, Autosys, VBA
- Workflow Design: BEPL, BPMN, Microsoft Flow

●● Market Risk ●●
- ChatBot, API Development -  Provide a tool to analysts to improve Hedge Funds monitoring
-Analytics on daily counterparty risk metrics

▶ Training of 150 risk Analysts – Python, SQL, Power BI

●● Model Risk ●●
- In progress: Design of a web-based tool to automate the creation of Model validation Report

▶ Continuous communication with the Business
            

    
    

    
        Show less
